But since it's dangerous in the dark,

261
00:15:34,390 --> 00:15:37,780
we have to do it at the
shrine, where there's light.

262
00:15:37,780 --> 00:15:41,520
Can't you just be happy that I 
let you do this test of courage?

263
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:42,870
So the rule is:

264
00:15:42,870 --> 00:15:47,180
you have to put a five yen coin on the edge
of the offering box and come back here.

265
00:15:47,180 --> 00:15:51,610
I also brought props for the scarer 
to use, so someone has to be the—

266
00:15:51,610 --> 00:15:52,960
Are you stupid?!

267
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:55,500
What's your problem all of a sudden?

268
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:58,910
Well, I figured you'd do something like this.

269
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:02,780
But I have no intention of 
doing something that silly.

270
00:16:02,780 --> 00:16:05,620
Aw, you're no fun.

271
00:16:05,620 --> 00:16:08,480
Just because you can't handle scary stuff...

272
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:11,540
I-I'm not scared or anything!

273
00:16:11,540 --> 00:16:14,820
I just think we might get 
spooked if a ghost shows up.

274
00:16:14,820 --> 00:16:17,890
There are no ghosts. 
That's why we need a scarer.

275
00:16:17,890 --> 00:16:20,740
Come on, we'll decide with 
rock-paper-scissors.

276
00:16:20,740 --> 00:16:22,160
If you don't play, you lose.

277
00:16:22,160 --> 00:16:23,460
W-Wait a second!

278
00:16:27,380 --> 00:16:28,730
Rock, paper...

279
00:16:28,730 --> 00:16:30,110
Scissors!

280
00:16:31,900 --> 00:16:33,020
I won!

281
00:16:33,020 --> 00:16:35,180
That means I'm the scarer, right?

282
00:16:35,180 --> 00:16:36,640
Man, I lost...

283
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:39,760
It just shows that I've 
been living my life right!

284
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:42,940
Oh, well. Go ahead and start 
getting ready, Nee-chan.

285
00:16:42,940 --> 00:16:46,910
Yeah, yeah. I don't want to scare 
you all so bad you start crying,

286
00:16:46,910 --> 00:16:48,350
so I'll go easy on you.

287
00:17:09,870 --> 00:17:14,810
Wh-What, so there's only one scarer?

288
00:17:14,810 --> 00:17:17,350
Anyway, I should hurry up and get ready.

289
00:17:18,260 --> 00:17:19,850
What's this sheet for?

290
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:24,930
Oh, I'm supposed to put 
this on and be a ghost?

291
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:27,860
Pretty typical setup Natsumi came up with...

292
00:17:28,940 --> 00:17:31,600
Jeez, why do I have to do this?

293
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:35,870
Huh? I can't see...

294
00:17:35,870 --> 00:17:37,340
It's dark!

295
00:17:38,960 --> 00:17:40,200
What is this?

296
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:42,910
The eyes are just drawn on with a marker!

297
00:17:42,910 --> 00:17:45,050
At least cut holes in it!

298
00:17:45,050 --> 00:17:47,430
Not being able to see is...

299
00:17:47,430 --> 00:17:50,520
...not scary, but let's 
find something else.

300
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:56,920
<i>I thought I heard footsteps behind me...</i>

301
00:17:57,460 --> 00:17:59,920
<i>I-It's just one of them coming up here, right?</i>

302
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:02,910
<i>No... This sensation...</i>

303
00:18:02,910 --> 00:18:05,930
<i>Th-There's no mistaking it.</i>

304
00:18:06,350 --> 00:18:07,930
<i>It's definitely...</i>

305
00:18:09,410 --> 00:18:10,700
<i>...a ghost!</i>

306
00:18:11,360 --> 00:18:13,170
I know you're behind m—

307
00:18:16,770 --> 00:18:20,110
What's going on? No one's there...

308
00:18:20,110 --> 00:18:23,010
What's goin' on?!

309
00:18:27,340 --> 00:18:29,350
I slipped into a country accent...

310
00:18:30,810 --> 00:18:33,380
I'll go where there's light.

311
00:18:33,380 --> 00:18:35,430
I can't stand the dark...

312
00:18:37,760 --> 00:18:40,930
Why did it turn out this way?

313
00:18:41,330 --> 00:18:45,940
If I had to do this, I'd rather have 
just done the test of courage...

314
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:52,110
Wh-Why is there a five yen coin...

315
00:18:52,110 --> 00:18:54,080
...when no one's been here?

316
00:18:54,080 --> 00:18:57,840
Wh-Who joined the game 
without telling me?

317
00:18:57,840 --> 00:19:00,410
Who's the mysterious participant?

318
00:19:04,830 --> 00:19:06,920
A black cat...

319
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:09,180
I like cats, but...

320
00:19:09,180 --> 00:19:11,230
I know what's going on!

321
00:19:11,230 --> 00:19:13,990
You're the one who joined the 
game without telling me!

322
00:19:14,590 --> 00:19:16,770
You're a monster cat!

323
00:19:18,140 --> 00:19:21,010
I-I-I'm sorry!

324
00:19:24,860 --> 00:19:26,690
The sheet again?!

325
00:19:26,690 --> 00:19:28,740
It's dark!

326
00:19:28,740 --> 00:19:30,780
S-Someone help me!

327
00:19:30,780 --> 00:19:31,950
It's dark!

328
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:35,520
Oh, Nii-chan's coming back.

329
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:37,920
Did Nee-chan do her job as the scarer?

330
00:19:40,930 --> 00:19:43,180
All right! Now it's my turn!

331
00:19:43,180 --> 00:19:44,330
Good luck.

332
00:19:44,330 --> 00:19:49,800
<i>So, I wonder how Nee-chan 
will try to scare me.</i>

333
00:19:50,180 --> 00:19:53,770
<i>Depending on how it goes, 
maybe I'll try to scare her.</i>

334
00:19:59,590 --> 00:20:09,450
Evil spirits, begone!

335
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,960
What's a ghost doing that for?

336
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:16,740
Evil spirits, begone!

337
00:20:21,290 --> 00:20:24,560
I'm a ghost!

338
00:20:31,910 --> 00:20:34,880
Armageddon!

339
00:20:35,310 --> 00:20:37,620
I'm glad we brought the fireworks.

340
00:20:37,620 --> 00:20:40,080
Yeah, aren't they pretty?

341
00:20:55,350 --> 00:20:57,140
Senpai, come join us.

342
00:20:57,970 --> 00:20:59,080
Huh?

343
00:21:02,520 --> 00:21:03,680
Here.

344
00:21:03,680 --> 00:21:04,680
Thanks.

345
00:22:13,130 --> 00:22:19,380
That's all for today

346
00:23:36,100 --> 00:23:38,000
<i>Want some corn?</i>

347
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:40,160
<i>This is probably the main 
reason why I'm poor.</i>

348
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:42,050
<i>Corn fishing!</i>

349
00:23:42,050 --> 00:23:43,240
<i>It's a clio-neko.</i>

350
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:45,970
<i>Wow, Nii-chan, you're pretty good!</i>

351
00:23:45,970 --> 00:23:48,820
<i>It looks like outer space </i><i>because</i> it's twisted.

